 including recently\nreleased annotations. The experimental results show that the KAIST\nMultispectral Pedestrian Benchmark with its improved annotations provides the\nbest basis to train a DCNN with good generalization ability compared to the\nother two multispectral datasets. On average, this detection model achieves a\nlog-average Miss Rate (MR) of 29.74 % evaluated on the reasonable test subsets\nof the three datasets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 May 2019 18:29:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-21"}
