 that reach the equivalent\nof 0.3 microseconds at 1400 MHz. This is because a spherical model ignores the\nlarge daily variations in electron density observed in the Solar wind. In the\nshort term, broadband observations or simultaneous observations at low\nfrequencies are the most promising way forward to correct for Solar-wind\ninduced delay variations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 May 2019 10:08:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-22"}
